Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, scatter over half the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{2}, then season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop the remaining North Indian style spice mix and half the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{150%g} into a large #bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then mix together. Pop the @British Chicken Thighs{4} into the bowl and mix well to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Once the chicken is browned, pop it onto a baking tray lined with #foil{}. Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125}. Trim the @Cucumber{1/2} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}. Pick the @Mint{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Halve the @Lime{1/2}.

Pop the tomatoes, cucumber, spring onion and half the mint into another medium #bowl. Squeeze over some lime juice, then add the @Olive Oil{} and season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine, then set aside your kachumber salad. Pop the remaining yoghurt into a small #bowl with the remaining mint, season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. When everything is nearly ready, halve the @Plain Naans{2} widthways then pop onto a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with a little @water{1%tsp} and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges. Thinly slice the cooked chicken. Pop half a naan on each #plate, then divide the sliced chicken, mint yoghurt and @Mango Chutney{1} between them. Top with the remaining naan halves and serve with the sweet potato wedges, kachumber salad and any lime wedges alongside. Enjoy!